==English==
===Noun===
'''race''' (''[[countable]] and uncountable''; ''plural'' '''races''')

#A contest between people, animals or vehicles where the goal is to reach some point before all of the others.
#A progressive movement toward a goal.
#A fast moving current of water.
#A group having common ancestors.
#A classification of human beings based on superficial traits such as skin colour, and shape of facial features
#(''uncountable'') Relations between different races (in the sense of classifications of human beings.
#:''Race was a significant issue during apartheid in South Africa.''

